OL,3,CGhana to lose #3 billion over anti-
OL,4,CLGBTQ+ bill, finance ministry warns
OL,6,FThe new bill could imprison people for
OL,7,Fmore than a decade for activities
OL,8,Fincluding public displays of affection
OL,9,Fand promotion of LGBTQ+ activities.
OL,11,FGay sex is already outlawed in , and
OL,12,Fcarries a three-year prison sentence,
OL,13,Fbut the anti-LGBTQ+ bill, formally
OL,14,Fcalled the Proper Human Sexual Rights
OL,15,Fand Ghanaian Family Values bill, is
OL,16,Fproposing much harsher punishments.
