OL,6,FThe possibility of the bill being
OL,7,Fimplemented has triggered backlash
OL,8,Ffrom Ghana's finance sector,
OL,9,Fdevelopment partners and international
OL,10,Ffinancial institutions, according to
OL,11,Fan internal government memo seen by
OL,12,FITV News.
OL,14,FMany have said that current financial
OL,15,Fagreements may be suspended if the
OL,16,Fbill is passed, and the loss to the
OL,17,FAfrican country's economy is currently
OL,18,Fset to add up to $3.8 billion (#3
OL,19,Fbillion), the finance ministry warned.
