OL,6,FGhana is already in dire financial
OL,7,Fstraits, and requested a bailout from
OL,8,Fthe International Monetary Fund (IMF)
OL,9,Fin May last year after the country's
OL,10,Fdebt burden became "unsustainable".
OL,12,FThe IMF approved a $3 billion (#2.36
OL,13,Fbillion) extended credit arrangement
OL,14,Ffor the West African nation to support
OL,15,Fits economic recovery in the wake of
OL,16,Fthe Covid-19 pandemic.
OL,18,FThose in favour of the bill say it
OL,19,Fwould help to protect children and
OL,20,Fpeople who are victims of abuse.
